            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I will give only one star to this because...\nHighly disappointed with this school.\n\nI am paying 82k for 1st standard(including transport and everything) and not getting what I was promised.\n\nMy child going standing in the bus.They took seats even when the bus is full.\n\n1st standard students have to read whole English and hindi sentences and then understand the meaning and write answer.Which is just not expected from them when they are actually able to read just 2..3 letter words. Even if they can read sentence the expectations are very high. Not happy with the syllabus.\n\nStudents have to walk 1st floor with 10 to 12 books,2tiffins and water bottle. Which is actually burdensome for little or elder students of 6 to 10 year old.\n\nNo proper management.We were called to meet teachers and after reaching school came to know that was a teachers day meeting.Then why did you call us??\n\nWe were having so much expectations as we shifted our child to cbsc from state board. But clearly telling you so much disappointed.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
